Class BTOProjectManager

java.lang.Object
com.group6.btoproject.BTOProjectManager
public class BTOProjectManager extends Object
Represents a central point to manage/access projects of a BTOSystem See BTOProject. See BTOSystem.

      public void requestApply(String projectId, String applicantUserId, BTOProjectTypeID typeId) throws RuntimeException
      Add an application to the project.
      Parameters:
      projectId - project to add the application to.
      applicantUserId - application to add.
      typeId - type id of the application.
      Throws:
      RuntimeException - If there exists an application that: - is PENDING and has the same applicantUserId. - is SUCCESSFUL and has the same applicantUserId. - is BOOKED and has the same applicantUserId.

    • transitionApplicationStatus

      public void transitionApplicationStatus(String projectId, String applicationId, BTOApplicationStatus status) throws RuntimeException
      Transition the status of an application.
      Parameters:
      projectId - project id.
      applicationId - application id.
      status - new status.
      Throws:
      RuntimeException - If the application: - Is not found. - Is PENDING and the new status is not SUCCESSFUL/UNSUCCESSFUL. - Is SUCCESSFUL and the new status is not BOOKED/UNSUCCESSFUL. - Is BOOKED and the new status is not UNSUCCESSFUL.

    • requestRegisterOfficer

      public void requestRegisterOfficer(String projectId, String userId) throws RuntimeException
      Add an HDB officer registration to the project.
      Parameters:
      projectId - project id.
      userId - HDB officer registration to add.
      Throws:
      RuntimeException - If there exists an officer registration that: - is SUCCESSFUL and has the same officerUserId (i.e. already managing this project). - is PENDING and has the same officerUserId.
